The old man ran his fingers through his white beard as he looked at the setting sun. He could take down the umbrella now and he’d probably have to put a shirt on over his swimming trunks. As he got off the sun lounger, he picked up the remains of the pina colada in the tall glass. It didn’t seem that long ago that they used to sit around a roaring fire on the ice, drinking strong Finnish vodka. Oh well, I suppose that Greta kid was right. The Arctic couldn’t last forever. That brought him on to his next...